    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_WONDER_THEOPETRACAVE_QUOTE">
      <Text>[NEWLINE]When one has finished building one's house, one suddenly realizes that in the process one has learned something that one really needed to know in the worst way -- before one began.[NEWLINE]  - Friedrich Nietzsche</Text>
    </Row>
    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_WONDER_THEOPETRACAVE_PEDIA">
      <Text>
        The Cave of Theopetra is unique amongst archeological sites, having taught us many of the early secrets on how man survived, lived, and died.
        [NEWLINE][NEWLINE]It is considered to be the oldest man-made structure found so far. It was inhabited for over 100,000 years due its prime location, great access to water, and a safe and protectable position.
        [NEWLINE][NEWLINE]It is here where we find many of the clues as to how Neanderthals were replaced by modern man. It is also here where we see the transition of a hunting and gathering lifestyle to eventually one of farming.
      </Text>
    </Row>
